records.addlTxt: Defendant Alicia R Bigelow in court, in custody.  Attorney Rumpf appears as friend of the court.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Rumpf requests Court extend payment plan in lieu of jail sentence.  State takes no position.  Court will amend the Judgment of Conviction to order defendant to pay $50/month commencing June 1, 2017 or alternate of 22 days jail.  Court will remove the community service component.

Defendant Alicia R Bigelow in court.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews the case on the record and notes that at the last hearing Judge Maxwell found that the defendant failed to comply with the order for community service and was ordered to serve 22 days in jail.  Ms. Bigelow advises she did not get notice of the hearing and provides an updated address.  State presents statements to the court and takes no position on the matter.  Court will quash the warrant and order that Ms. Bigelow serve the 22 days in jail as ordered by the judge.  Atty. Rumpf appears as friend of the court and is asking the court to set the matter for review before the Judge and not impose the 22 day jail sanction at this time.  Court finds based on the judgment of conviction it will impose the 22 days jail as ordered by the judge.  Court orders that the defendant be taken into immediate custody to serve the 22 days jail.  Court will also set the matter for review before the judge.  Review hearing scheduled for April 24, 2017 at 10:30 am.
